## Design Decisions

<!-- Document key design choices for the NZ trip page here -->
<!-- Format: - [DATE] Decision: Description and rationale -->
- [2026-03-01] INDEPENDENCE: Built completely standalone page (no BaseLayout, no shared fonts/styles) to allow fresh, travel-optimized design
- [2026-03-01] TYPOGRAPHY: System fonts (-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', etc.) for excellent mobile readability and performance; no custom font dependencies
- [2026-03-01] COLOR PALETTE: Green-focused (emerald/teal accents, #065f46–#10b981) for outdoor/adventure feel; type-specific highlights (blue flights, orange activities, etc.)
- [2026-03-01] STICKY NAV: Horizontal scrolling day tabs with active state highlighting; scroll-margin-top on sections for proper anchor jumping below nav
- [2026-03-01] DARK MODE: Full prefers-color-scheme support; tested light/dark backgrounds, text contrast, card colors
- [2026-03-01] TIMELINE LAYOUT: Left-aligned vertical timeline with colored circles per item type; gradient line connects activities visually
- [2026-03-01] QUICK REFERENCE: Copy-to-clipboard buttons for hotel addresses; emergency contacts in red alert card; NZ phrases in grid for learning
- [2026-03-01] MOBILE-FIRST: All scoped styles; `overflow: auto !important` on body to ensure scrolling works; flexible grid (repeat(auto-fit, minmax(...)))
- [2026-03-01] DATA STRUCTURE: Typed TypeScript interfaces (TimelineItem, Day) in frontmatter; helper functions for colors, icons, Maps links
- [2026-03-01] NO FRAMEWORKS: Pure HTML + vanilla JS for nav active state; no React/Vue dependencies; minimal ~50 lines of JS for scroll tracking

